    "message_1": "For this numerical problem, consider the following system of linear equations with noisy data:\n```\n4.2x + 2.9y + 1.5z = 34.8\n3.1x - 5.5y + 2.3z = -12.3\n6.3x + 3.8y - 7.1z = 42.7\n```\nwhere the actual coefficient of each variable is within ± 0.2 of the given value, and the actual right-hand side of each equation is within ± 1.0 of the given value. Use linear algebra methods to find the best estimate of the solution vector `[x y z]`.",
    "message_2": "To find the best estimate of the solution vector `[x y z]`, we can use the least squares method. First, let's rewrite the system of linear equations in matrix form:\n\n```\nA * X = B\n```\n\nwhere\n\n```\nA = | 4.2  2.9  1.5 |\n    | 3.1 -5.5  2.3 |\n    | 6.3  3.8 -7.1 |\n\nX = | x |\n    | y |\n    | z |\n\nB = | 34.8  |\n    | -12.3 |\n    | 42.7  |\n```\n\nNow, we can use the least squares method to find the best estimate of the solution vector `X`. The least squares solution is given by:\n\n```\nX = (A^T * A)^(-1) * A^T * B\n```\n\nwhere `A^T` is the transpose of matrix `A`, and `A^T * A` is the normal matrix.\n\nLet's compute the transpose of matrix `A`:\n\n```\nA^T = |  4.2  3.1  6.3 |\n      |  2.9 -5.5  3.8 |\n      |  1.5  2.3 -7.1 |\n```\n\nNow, let's compute the normal matrix `A^T * A`:\n\n```\nA^T * A = |  4.2*4.2+3.1*3.1+6.3*6.3   4.2*2.9+3.1*(-5.5)+6.3*3.8   4.2*1.5+3.1*2.3+6.3*(-7.1) |\n          |  2.9*4.2+(-5.5)*3.1+3.8*6.3   2.9*2.9+(-5.5)*(-5.5)+3.8*3.8   2.9*1.5+(-5.5)*2.3+3.8*(-7.1) |\n          |  1.5*4.2+2.3*3.1+(-7.1)*6.3   1.5*2.9+2.3*(-5.5)+(-7.1)*3.8   1.5*1.5+2.3*2.3+(-7.1)*(-7.1) |\n\nA^T * A = |  61.98  -1.61 -41.66 |\n          |  -1.61  54.86 -11.66 |\n          | -41.66 -11.66  54.35 |\n```\n\nNow, let's compute the inverse of the normal matrix `(A^T * A)^(-1)`:\n\n```\n(A^T * A)^(-1) = |  0.0181  0.0003  0.0137 |\n                 |  0.0003  0.0183  0.0043 |\n                 |  0.0137  0.0043  0.0201 |\n```\n\nNow, let's compute the product `(A^T * A)^(-1) * A^T`:\n\n```\n(A^T * A)^(-1) * A^T = |  0.0181*4.2+0.0003*2.9+0.0137*1.5   0.0181*3.1+0.0003*(-5.5)+0.0137*2.3   0.0181*6.3+0.0003*3.8+0.0137*(-7.1) |\n                        |  0.0003*4.2+0.0183*2.9+0.0043*1.5   0.0003*3.1+0.0183*(-5.5)+0.0043*2.3   0.0003*6.3+0.0183*3.8+0.0043*(-7.1) |\n                        |  0.0137*4.2+0.0043*2.9+0.0201*1.5   0.0137*3.1+0.0043*(-5.5)+0.0201*2.3   0.0137*6.3+0.0043*3.8+0.0201*(-7.1) |\n\n(A^T * A)^(-1) * A^T = |  0.0767 -0.0081  0.1235 |\n                        |  0.0531 -0.0959  0.0675 |\n                        |  0.0635  0.0419 -0.1423 |\n```\n\nFinally, let's compute the least squares solution `X = (A^T * A)^(-1) * A^T * B`:\n\n```\nX = |  0.0767*34.8-0.0081*(-12.3)+0.1235*42.7 |\n    |  0.0531*34.8-0.0959*(-12.3)+0.0675*42.7 |\n    |  0.0635*34.8+0.0419*(-12.3)-0.1423*42.7 |\n\nX = |  2.6723 |\n    | -1.1041 |\n    |  3.4709 |\n```\n\nSo, the best estimate of the solution vector `[x y z]` is `[2.6723, -1.1041, 3.4709]`."
